 NO fewer than seven policemen were feared killed on Sunday in a ghastly auto crash on Kaduna-Zaria highway. Eyewitnesses said the crash occurred around 4:30pm, close to Jaji Military Cantonment, when a speeding 18-seater bus conveying policemen somersaulted. Our correspondent reports that the policemen were heading towards Zaria from Kaduna when the accident happened. An eyewitness said, “It was a terrible accident because I counted about seven bodies of policemen in the middle of the road. Two were seriously injured while others survived.” Public spokesman ASP Muhammed Jalige told journalists that they had sent teams of policemen to the scene to find out what happened.  